05/28/2024,748.1337(b) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,08/09/2024,08/04/2024,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium Low,Yes,"The service plan report reviewed for this investigation had several areas left blank to include summary of goals, needs and strengths sections, summary progress for goals, medication list, triggers, target dates, emotional disorders, and missing signatures.","An email was sent with the following correctives:
Per your request, corrections for Investigation 

On Friday, August 02, 2024, A Promising Journey received a letter pertaining to per said investigation stating standard: 

748.1337 (b) Initial Service Plan-Document in the childs record to include preliminary service plan requirements

It was determined that the Service Plan was missing several blank areas including the summary of goals, needs and strengths sections, summary of progress goals, medication list, triggers, target dates, emotional disorders, as well as missing signatures. 

A Promising Journey (APJ) sets policies and procedures for residents/staff to increase accountability, professionalism, progress, and avoid unnecessary crisis and/or violations.

Service Plan documentation is also a part of policies and procedures as a method of ensuring that APJ monitors and records all of residents progress and performances.

Moving Forward

The Professional Level Service Provider/Case Manager/Licensed Child Care Administrator will ensure that each childs service plan is completely individualized and detailed to ensure that the childs needs are evaluated and met in all areas of service and need, including but not limited to signatures.

Failing to do so may result in staff being removed from their work schedule pending results from investigation and/or allowed to work in another area. 



